      "writtenOn": "2020-11-09T22:07:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This will do a lot of work on every call even though configs mostly don\u0027t change.\nThink about ways to avoid expensive fetching of config data and writing it to datastore if it\u0027s not necessary.\n\nIdeas:\n* ask LUCI Config first for config *revision*. If it\u0027s the same as stored in ProjectConfig entity, quick exit. No transactions required. Strictly speaking, we can even use config hash (as computed by luci config) to do even less work.\n\n* before writing config group to datastore, check if datastore already contains the entity. Since these are idempotent, allows to skip work.",
      "revId": "56d2553ba16e49dc4dc416d5e12eb1c80a393b91",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
