      "lineNbr": 155,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-09T22:07:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This should be done outside of a transaction:\n * amount of data written can eventually be \u003e10MiB (trans limit)\n * op is idempotent and won\u0027t affect any other ops (by design 👍). Making it atomic gives us nothing.\n * but costs us by increasing chance of failure: suppose we have 2 big config groups. Failing to write 2nd one, will undo the write of the first.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 155,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 155,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "56d2553ba16e49dc4dc416d5e12eb1c80a393b91",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a794fa0a_c7ab0119",
        "filename": "cv/appengine/internal/config/refresh.go",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 155,
      "author": {
        "id": 1381059
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-14T20:28:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed % one concern. \n\nMoving it out of a transaction may cause the EVersion goes out of sync and may even cause dangling ConfigGroups. Imagining a scenario:\n  * T0: Assuming we have H0 + V0 in datastore\n  * T1: config changes in LUCI Config\n  * T2: refresh job starts: CV writes ConfigGroups with H1+V1 but fail to write ProjectConfig with H1+V1 fails\n  * T3: config has been changed in LUCI Config,\n  * T4: refresh job starts: CV writes ConfigGroups and Project Config with H1\u0027+V1.\n  * T5: config change has been rolled back\n  * T6: ConfigGroup with H1 has V1. However, CV needs to re-write it again with V2\n\n\nTherefore, I create a new `ConfigHashInfo` entity to keep the mutable information while making `ConfigGroup` entity completely immutable.",
      "parentUuid": "3af9be23_45bdfe33",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 155,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 155,
        "endChar": 31
      },
      "revId": "56d2553ba16e49dc4dc416d5e12eb1c80a393b91",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
